  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Consolidation of a public agenda for sport, tourism and legacy for the city of Brasilia in light of the 2016 Olympic Games</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As Brasilia will receive several international delegations and tourists around the 2016 Olympic Games, the Government of the City of Brasilia has approached UNESCO to develop a cooperation project focused on three main axis: 1) Strenghtnening the incipient local sport policy with investments in initiatives for the youth; 2) Designing policy recommendations for local touristic and heritage policies vis a vis the register of Brasilia in the UNESCO World Heritage List (1983); and 3) Support the newly created Brasilia secretariat of sport and culture with temporary structures and cultural events in the vicinities of the Brasilia National Stadium during the Olympic Games.</narrative>
  </description>
